px;">The edict was hardly surprising; CNN has been tilting, in fits and sta=
rts, toward a less polarizing posture ever since Warner Bros. Discovery too=
k over the network in 2022=E2=80=94either because that=E2=80=99s what
<strong>John Malone </strong>wants, or it=E2=80=99s what more than half of =
the country appears to want, or just because it makes for a larger business=
 opportunity. Nevertheless, when compared to the past two inaugurations, th=
e result was an awkward volte-face that felt almost like a hostage video. O=
n Monday, star journalists who years ago railed against Trump now offered l=
ittle scrutiny whatsoever. <strong>Oliver Darcy</strong>, the former CNN me=
