px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Depending on who yo=
u ask, this is either a long-overdue correction to the polarizing leftward =
pivot and emotional hysteria of the previous decade, or a gross abdication =
of the
Fourth Estate=E2=80=99s responsibilities to hold power accountable. (A simi=
lar debate is ensuing about Meta=E2=80=99s decision to forgo fact-checking.=
) Either way, it is indisputably awkward=E2=80=94<em>most </em>notably for =
the journalists whose righteous indignation was either performative then or=
 easily bought off now.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0<=
/p><p style=3D"margin:0;">In any event, Thompson=E2=80=99s decree was yet a=
nother blow to morale for a network that now sits alongside Job, Antoine Do=
inel, and
Umberto D. Ferrari on the Mount Rushmore of Eternal Suffering. And the hits=
 kept coming. After being restricted to supplying background noise for a pi=
votal moment in world history, CNN learned the next day that it had average=
d less than <em>one-fifth </em>of the audience it had during <strong>Joe Bi=
den</strong>=E2=80=99s inauguration just four years ago. Between 11:30 a.m.=
 and 1 p.m. ET on Monday, a mere 1.7 million people were watching CNN, down=
 from 10 million in 2021. Meanwhile, more than 10 million
watched Trump=E2=80=99s second inauguration on Fox News.</p></div>
